Protocol.text: Human atherosclerotic plaques from internal carotid artery were obtained from patients undergoing carotid endarterectomy due to high-grade stenosis. Plaques were removed en bloc in longitudinal endarterectomy, drained with saline and cut into 5 longitudinal slices. One of these was stored in -80°C until total cellular RNA was extracted by using Trizol® reagent (Invitrogen Life Technologies, Inc. Carlsbad, CA) according to manufacturer's recommandations. Shortly, plaques were homogenized in Trizol® using Ultra-Turrax T25 homogenizer (IKA Laboratorioteknik) and subsequent steps were done according to the routine protocol except for an extra centrifugation before addition of chloroform to get rid of unhomogenized material and the majority of DNA. Total RNA was further purified by silica colums (RNeasy; Qiagen, Valencia, CA) according to the manufacturer's instructions. Quality was controlled by measuring A260/280 by spectrophotometry and the 18S/26S ratio by microcapillary electrophoresis (Bioanalyzer 2100; Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, CA).
Protocol.name: EXTPRTCL_HeCES

Protocol.text:
Target labelling was carried out following the instructions and recommendations described in the GeneChip Expression Analysis: Technical Manual, 2001 (see for details). All procedures were done according to the manufacturers instructions.

5 μg of good quality total RNA was used as a starting material in the RT reaction. Primer 5'-GGCCAGTGAATTGTAATACGACTCACTATAGGGAGGCGG-(dT)24-3' (100 pmol/reaction) was used in conjunction with SuperScrip Choise System for cDNA Synthesis (Invitrogen Life Technologies, Inc. Carlsbad, CA) to produce double stranded cDNA.

Double stranded cDNA was purified using phenol/chloroform/isoamylalcohol extraction in Phase Lock Gel tubes (PLG I - heavy 1,5 ml) followed by ethanol precipitation with 0.5 μl of Pellet Paint (Novagen, Madison, WI) as a carrier.

In vitro transcription was used to produce biotin-labelled cRNA by using double-stranded cDNA as a template in the presence of biotinylated UTP and CTP, using an ENZO BioArray HighYield RNA Transcript Labeling Kit (ENZO Diagnostics, Farmingdale, NY).

Labelled cRNA was purified using RNeasy Mini Kit (Qiagen, Valencia, CA) and fragmented by metal-induced hydrolysis in a reaction containing 0.5μg/μl of the labelled product in a fragmentation buffer (200mM Tris-acetate, pH 8.1, 500mM KOAc, 150 mM MgOAc) and heating the mixture 35 min in 94°C.

The quality of RNA was monitored in different stages of the labelling procedure by absorbance measures (A260/A280) and partly by microcapillary electrophoresis (Bioanalyzer 2100; Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, CA) using RNA 6000 LabChip kit (Caliper Technologies, MountainView, CA). All incubations were carried on in thermomixer (Thermomixer comfort; Eppendorf AG, Hamburg, Germany).
Protocol.name: LABELPRTCL_HeCESbilaterals

Protocol.text:
Target hybridization was carried out according to the instructions and recommendations of the Affymetrix GeneChip Analysis: Technical Manual, 2001.

10 μg of fragmented cRNA was hybridized to an microarray in a reaction volyme of 200 μl.

HYBRIDIZATION COCKTAIL

Fragmented cRNA 15 μg

Control oligonucleotide B2 (Affymetrix, Santa Clara, CA) 50pM (final concentration)

20xEucaryotic Hybridization Controls (bioB, bioC, bioD and cre) (Affymetrix, Santa Clara, CA) 1.5, 5, 25 and 100 pM respectively (final concentrations)

Herring Sperm DNA (Promega corp., Madison, WI) 0.1 mg/ml (final concentration)

Acetylated BSA (Invitrogen Life Technologies, Inc. Carlsbad, CA) 0.5 mg/ml (final concentration)

2x Hybridization buffer (200mM MES, 1M [Na+], 20mM EDTA, 0.01% Tween 20) 150 μl

H2O (Ambion, Austin, TX) ADD. 300 μl

Pre-Hybridization was performed with 1x hybridization buffer for 15 min with 60rpm rotation at 45°C in GeneChip Hybridization Oven.

The hybridization cocktail was heated to 99°C for 5 min and placed to cool in the above mentioned hybridization oven for 5 min and finally centrifuged for 5 min 13 000 x g RT.

200 μl of the pre-treated hybridization cocktail was added to the array and hybridized for 16 hours in the GeneChip Hybridization Oven at 45°C with 60 rpm rotation.

WASHING AND STAINING

Affymetrix Antibody Amplification Washing and Staining Protocol was used for staining.

SAPE Solution Mix 2x 600 μl

2xMES Stain buffer (200 mM MES, 1M [Na+], 0.05% Tween 20) 600 μl

Acetylated BSA 2mg/ml (final concentration)

Streptavidin-Phycoerythrin (SAPE) (Molecular Probes, Eugene, OR) 10μg/ml (final concentration)

H2O ADD. 1200 μl

Antibody Solution, 300 μl

2xMES Stain Solution 300 μl

Acetylated BSA 2 mg/ml (final concentration)

Normal Goat IgG (Sigma-Aldrich, St. Luis, MO) 0.1 mg/ml (final concetration)

Anti-streptavidin antibody (goat), biotinylated (Vector Laboratories, Burlingame, CA) 3 μg/ml

H2O ADD. 600 μl

Affymetrix GeneChip Fluidics Station 450 was used to automatically stain the arrays according to wash and stain protocol EukGE_WS2v4.

For a detailed description see: GeneChip Expression Analysis: Technical Manual, 2001.
Protocol.name: HYBRIDPRTCL_HeCESbilaterals

Protocol.text:
Expression data generated by the microarrays (HG-U95Av2; Affymetrix, Santa Clara, CA) were analyzed by using Microarray Suite v5.0 (MAS; Affymetrix). The analysis setting was such that each symptomatic plaque was compared to an asymptomatic one from the same patient resulting in four comparison pairs.

All arrays were scaled to an arbitrary value of 100 by using all probe sets, no other normalization was applied. A Signal, a Detection call and p-value were calculated for each array. For each four intraindividual comparisons between asymptomatic and symptomatic samples, a Change call and p-value and Signal Log Ratio (SLR) were also calculated. Default values for Tau, Alpha 1 and 2, Perturbation, Gamma 1 and 2 were used.

Differentially expressed genes were identified by filtering using following criteria: 1) transcript expressed at a reliable level (the Detection call = present) in either CP from three patients, 2) the Change call = increased or decreased with a p-value < 0.001 or > 0.999, respectively, 3) the Signal 2-fold increased (SLR > 1) or decreased (SLR < 1) in at least three comparison pairs or the mean-fold change > 2 for all four comparisons.

Experiment.name: HeCESbilaterals: intra-individual differences between asymptomatic and symptomatic carotid plaques

Description.text: We compared gene expression profiles between asymptomatic and symptomatic atherosclerotic plaques from the same patient. This was accomplished by analyzing carotid plaques from four patients with bilateral high-grade carotid artery stenoses one being symptomatic (TIA or stroke) and the other asymptomatic.

After scanning, array images were assessed by eye to confirm scanner alignment and the absence of image artifacts. Values (mean±SD) for quality control measures, including average background (44±4), raw Noise (Q) values (1.50±0.14), scaling factor (2.00±0.95), percent present (46±3) and spike controls, were confirmed to be within acceptable limits. For 3'/5' ratios of GAPDH and beta-actin, samples from patient No 4 showed increased ratios (3.11-6.46) indicating degradation of the 5' ends of mRNAs. These samples were kept in the analysis because of the rarity of bilateral samples and similar trend in both samples to be compared. In addition, the preferential assignment of Affymetrix probe sets to the 3' ends decreases the likelihood of moderate mRNA degradation effecting the hybridization results.
